FBIS4-534 "drafr071_a_94002" FBIS-AFR-94-071 Daily Report 8 Apr 1994 CENTRAL AFRICA Chad Agreement Reached on Libyan Withdrawl From Aozou Agreement Reached on Libyan Withdrawl From Aozou AB0904121994 Ndjamena Radiodiffusion Nationale Tchadienne in French 1900 GMT 8 Apr 94 AB0904121994 Ndjamena Radiodiffusion Nationale Tchadienne French BFN [Excerpt] Interior and Security Minister Abderaman Izzo returned to Ndjamena this afternoon from Tripoli. The interior minister led a Chadian Government delegation which held discussions with their Libyan counterpart. The discussions ended in an agreement on the withdrawal of Libyan troops from the Aozou Strip. According to Minister Abderaman Izzo, the discussions were not easy and the Chadian delegation had to compel the Libyans to leave Aozou, in accordance with the decision of the International Court of Justice on the issue. [passage omitted]
